1
00:00:35,740 --> 00:00:37,200
给我乖乖待着
Stay down!

2
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:44,120
不准乱动
Don't move!

3
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:50,750
搞定
Yeah!

4
00:00:57,550 --> 00:00:59,720
求救求救 这里是顽童二号
Mayday! Mayday! This is the Sawyer-Two.

5
00:00:59,720 --> 00:01:01,180
我们遭遇海盗攻击
We're under attack by pirates.

6
00:01:01,180 --> 00:01:02,640
请求即刻救援
Requesting an immediate aid.

7
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:09,730
大家总说每人各有特长
They say everybody's good at something.

8
00:01:09,730 --> 00:01:12,150
而我 能与鱼类沟通
Me? I talk to fish.

9
00:01:12,150 --> 00:01:14,320
我也因此结识好友暴风
That's how I met my friend, Storm.

10
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:19,070
我需要坐骑时它总会出现
He's always there when I need a lift.

11
00:01:31,090 --> 00:01:33,920
有些人因此觉得我很搞笑 但我不在乎
Some people think that makes me a joke. But I don't care.

12
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:36,670
知道为什么吗? 因为我还有别的强项
You know why? 'Cause I'm also good at something else.

13
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:42,640
那就是擅长爆头
And that's breaking heads.

14
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:52,440
老爸单挑所有海盗
Pow! Papa took on all the pirates.

15
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:54,070
我说:"你们海盗以为..."
I was like, "Well, the pirates think that..."

16
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:57,110
你老爸打趴他们
Papa kicked their butts.

17
00:02:02,370 --> 00:02:04,370
那些杂碎根本毫无胜算
Those chum lickers didn't stand a chance.

18
00:02:06,540 --> 00:02:08,330
把他们打成满地找牙的猪头
Papa kicked their asses and took their names.

19
00:02:08,620 --> 00:02:10,330
好耶 太棒了
Yeah! Come on!

20
00:02:13,460 --> 00:02:14,130
小心
Watch out.

21
00:02:19,260 --> 00:02:21,510
抱歉老爹 是我不对
Sorry, Pops. My bad.

22
00:02:21,970 --> 00:02:24,680
对了 那是我儿子 小亚瑟
Oh, yeah, this is my son, Arthur Jr.

23
00:02:25,510 --> 00:02:27,890
四年前 我的人生完全改变
See, four years ago, everything changed.

24
00:02:27,890 --> 00:02:29,890
我遇见一位美女 坠入爱河
I met a woman, fell in love,

25
00:02:30,350 --> 00:02:31,350
然后转眼间...
and the next thing I know,

26
00:02:31,350 --> 00:02:33,980
我们已结婚生子
we're getting married and having a kid.

27
00:02:33,980 --> 00:02:36,530
这个小家伙是我此生最棒的礼物
This little guy's the best thing that ever happened to me.

28
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:43,200
但这小子 他从不乖乖睡觉
But this kid, he doesn't sleep.

29
00:02:44,740 --> 00:02:46,410
你尿布里面藏了什么?
What you got in there, huh?

30
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:49,370
好了...
Okay...

31
00:02:50,830 --> 00:02:52,500
而且他总是命中目标
And he never misses.

32
00:02:53,130 --> 00:02:53,960
搞什么...
What the...

33
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,040
所以我总是超早起床
And then, I'm up at the crack of dawn

34
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:57,880
因为除了结婚生子之外
because on top of getting married and having a kid...

35
00:02:57,880 --> 00:02:59,420
我还终于找到一份工作
...I finally got a job.

36
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:01,680
没错
That's right.

37
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:04,300
在下正是亚特兰提斯之王
I'm the king of freaking Atlantis.

38
00:03:07,140 --> 00:03:08,470
知道我是怎么坐上这位置的?
How did I score that, you asked?

39
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:13,150
我阻止我小弟欧姆攻击陆地世界
Well, I stopped my brother, Orm, from attacking the surface world.

40
00:03:13,650 --> 00:03:16,150
在过程中 我剥夺了他的王位
And in doing so, I claimed the throne from him.

41
00:03:17,570 --> 00:03:18,690
一开始我以为
At first I was all like...

42
00:03:18,690 --> 00:03:20,240
好耶
Yeah!

43
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,320
领海的掌控权以前都是...
The territorial waters are long held...

44
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:26,530
然后我发现当国王其实没那么好玩
But then, as it turned out, being king wasn't all it was cracked up to be.

45
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:31,370
整天有开不完的政治会议
It's just meetings all day and politics.

46
00:03:31,370 --> 00:03:33,500
快无聊死了 我都不知道对着盐海国王时
I'm so bored, I don't even know which end of the Brine King

47
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:35,170
眼睛该往哪看
I'm supposed to be looking at half the time.

48
00:03:38,210 --> 00:03:39,960
好耶 真是太赞了
Yeah! That was awesome!

49
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:41,380
好像这还不够糟糕
And if that's not bad enough,

50
00:03:41,380 --> 00:03:43,680
我更发现还有一个以前没人
turns out there's this whole Council of Houses thing

51
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:45,090
跟我提过的众议院
that nobody told me about.

52
00:03:45,090 --> 00:03:47,640
他们有权否决所有我想做的事
Which basically gets to shoot down everything I want to do.

53
00:03:48,810 --> 00:03:50,430
还好有我的小家伙作伴
The only thing that makes all the hard work

54
00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:53,520
才不枉我那份苦差事和不眠夜
and sleepless nights worthwhile is hanging with my little man.

55
00:03:54,810 --> 00:03:56,020
你没射中
Hey! You missed me!

56
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:02,110
当然这工作也有好玩的地方
But of course, there are fun parts of the job.

57
00:04:05,860 --> 00:04:08,280
我得以用我的方式来维持海洋安全
I get to keep the sea safe the best way I know how.

58
00:04:12,330 --> 00:04:14,920
特别是我还破获了几个非法铁笼格斗
Especially when I get to take down an illegal cage fight or two.

59
00:04:20,670 --> 00:04:24,430
但不管我有多成功 还是会搞砸一些小事
But for everything I get right, something else gets screwed up.

60
00:04:35,140 --> 00:04:36,060
喵的...
Ah, fu...

61
00:05:02,460 --> 00:05:03,960
-好耶 -给你
- Oh, yeah. - Here you go.

62
00:05:18,650 --> 00:05:21,270
他会需要手足来陪他玩
So... he's gonna need a little brother or sister to play with.

63
00:05:25,490 --> 00:05:26,900
他有一只狗
He's got a dog.

64
00:05:27,530 --> 00:05:29,030
我是认真的
Hey, I'm serious.

65
00:05:30,450 --> 00:05:33,450
我亲眼看到你小时候有多寂寞
I saw how lonely it was for you growing up.

66
00:05:33,450 --> 00:05:34,950
身为独生子
An only child.

67
00:05:36,620 --> 00:05:38,870
我很遗憾没能给你更多手足
I always regretted I couldn't give you that.

68
00:05:39,790 --> 00:05:42,090
别对自己太严苛
Yeah, well, don't be too hard on yourself.

69
00:05:43,090 --> 00:05:45,460
结果我有个继弟 却是个混帐
Turns out I have a brother and he's a total dick bag.

70
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:46,760
别这样
Come on.

71
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:51,350
你跟欧姆的关系是特殊案例
Your relationship with Orm isn't how it usually is.

72
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:57,140
兄弟姐妹吵架很正常 但大家总归是家人
Sure, siblings bicker and fight... but at the end of the day, they're family.

73
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:01,190
必要时应该能指望他们帮忙
You should be able to count on them for help.

74
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:05,900
是喔 若要找帮手我还是宁愿选狗
Yeah, well, I'll still take the dog over him any day.

75
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:13,700
喂 你快看
Hey, look at that.

76
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:25,460
不是吧
Holy crap.

77
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:35,560
小宝贝 你是在跟鱼说话吗?
Hi, baby boy. Are you talking to the fishies?

78
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:42,190
天啊老爹 这太让我惊喜了
Oh, man. Pops, this is blowing my mind.

79
00:06:43,230 --> 00:06:46,320
我这辈子都希望能跟人分享这天赋
My whole life I've wanted to share this gift with someone.

80
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:50,950
儿子 你和我 我们与众不同 我们很特别
Yeah, but you and me, son, we're different. We're special.

81
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:54,530
我们是陆地与海洋间的桥梁
We're connected to the land and the sea.

82
00:06:54,530 --> 00:06:58,750
我等不及要介绍你认识 世上所有神奇生物
I can't wait to introduce you to all the majestic creatures on our planet.

83
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:01,540
让你知道这世界能有多棒
And show you how awesome this world can be.

84
00:07:02,540 --> 00:07:03,710
对 你我一起
Yeah, you and me.

85
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:03,190
我交叉比对了沈博士的座标 结果一无所获
I cross-referenced the coordinates from Dr. Shin. Nothing.

86
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:05,730
还是没能在冰下找到亚特兰提斯遗迹
Still no sign of Atlantean remnants under the ice.

87
00:08:06,270 --> 00:08:09,020
看来他又带我们白跑一趟了
Looks like he's led us on another wild goose chase.

88
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:31,300
只要我一天不修好动力装甲 海王就能多苟活一天
Every day I don't fix my power suit is another day Aquaman gets to live.

89
00:08:35,300 --> 00:08:36,760
再查一次
Check again.

90
00:08:37,550 --> 00:08:39,970
这次很接近了 我有预感
We're close this time. I can feel it.

91
00:08:47,190 --> 00:08:52,110
探险日志第463日 史蒂芬沈博士录音
Expedition log day 463, Dr. Stephen Shin recording.

92
00:08:52,110 --> 00:08:55,740
为了寻找亚特兰提斯 我走遍了全世界
My quest for Atlantis has brought me to the ends of the earth.

93
00:08:55,740 --> 00:08:58,160
大卫凯恩逐渐失去耐心
David Kane is losing his patience.

94
00:08:58,780 --> 00:09:02,290
若我不尽快找到他想要的 亚特兰提斯科技
If I don't turn up the Atlantean technology he's looking for soon,

95
00:09:02,290 --> 00:09:04,790
他们大概会...
they're probably going to... um...

96
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:10,960
还是不提那个了 我相信一切都会顺利的
You know what, let's not even go there. I'm sure everything will be fine.

97
00:09:22,970 --> 00:09:24,850
沈博士 快来看
Dr. Shin, take a look at this.

98
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:27,390
拜托告诉我你有线索了
Please tell me you found something.

99
00:09:27,940 --> 00:09:29,730
地震仪上的读数超扯的
Seismic array is going crazy.

100
00:09:29,730 --> 00:09:31,070
震央在哪?
Where's the epicenter?

101
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:33,400
就在我们脚下
We're standing on it.

102
00:09:56,550 --> 00:09:57,550
快逃啊
Run!

103
00:10:46,020 --> 00:10:48,560
发生什么事了 是地震吗?
What just happened? An earthquake?

104
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:51,730
不是 应该是一片冰盖脱落了
No. I think it was a piece of ice sheet breaking off.

105
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:30,980
快点 站起来
Come on. Get up.

106
00:11:33,270 --> 00:11:35,230
-我的脚踝好像断了 -快点 我们走
- I think I broke my ankle! - Come on. Let's go!

107
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:37,570
快点起来 我们得走了
Come on, get up. Go, we gotta go! We gotta go!

108
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:41,700
快点 我们得离开 快点
Come on, we gotta move! Come on!

109
00:11:51,330 --> 00:11:53,500
（发射讯号）

110
00:12:02,420 --> 00:12:03,970
拜托 拜托 救我
Please, please. No, no!

111
00:12:03,970 --> 00:12:05,590
救我 拜托 别放手
Help, please! Don't let go!

112
00:12:36,460 --> 00:12:38,250
你发生什么事了?
What the hell happened to you?

113
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:41,800
那后面有恐怖的东西
There's something back there.

114
00:12:56,060 --> 00:12:57,730
太神奇了
Astounding.

115
00:12:58,730 --> 00:13:00,820
读数显示下面有东西
My readings show something's down here.

116
00:13:00,820 --> 00:13:03,820
尺寸大到可能是亚特兰提斯船舰
And it's definitely big enough to be an Atlantean ship.

117
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:07,070
若真的是 就可能在上面 找到能修理你动力装甲的科技
If it is, we might be able to scavenge the tech you need to fix your suit.

118
00:13:07,990 --> 00:13:10,450
这地方怎么可能真实存在?
How is this place even possible?

119
00:13:10,830 --> 00:13:14,500
在地球持续升温前 这里应该被冰封了
This was all probably solid ice until we started heating the planet.

120
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:18,960
感谢温室效应 对吧?
Well, thank God for global warming, am I right?

121
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:21,960
那个 应该不算什么好事
Uh, yeah, that's not exactly a good thing.

122
00:13:39,770 --> 00:13:41,520
足迹都往下走
The tracks lead down there.

123
00:13:43,230 --> 00:13:44,360
穿上装备
Suit up.

124
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:47,450
等等 足迹都往下走
Wait. The tracks lead down there,

125
00:13:47,450 --> 00:13:50,990
意思是怪兽也在下面
which means... the monster's down there.

126
00:13:56,660 --> 00:13:58,750
好吧 我猜我们要下去
Okay. I guess we're going down there.

127
00:14:24,110 --> 00:14:25,610
太不可思议了
I don't believe this.

128
00:14:27,150 --> 00:14:29,070
这是某种建物
It's a structure of some kind.

129
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,240
冰里埋藏着更多东西
And there's more buried in the ice.

130
00:14:32,990 --> 00:14:35,410
本来以为我们只会找到船舰
Here I thought we were just going to find a ship.

131
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:39,710
-所有人 散开搜寻 -收到
- Everyone, fan out and search. - Yes, sir.

132
00:14:39,710 --> 00:14:42,670
我们侥幸撞见大发现了 博士
We've stumbled upon something big here, doc.

133
00:14:46,050 --> 00:14:48,510
这肯定有几千年的历史
This has to be a few thousand years old.

134
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:50,260
太神奇了
Astounding.

135
00:15:58,240 --> 00:16:00,000
这到底是什么地方?
What is this place?

136
00:16:00,790 --> 00:16:06,500
终于 你找到这里了
At last, you are here.

137
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:39,490
将我从监禁中释放
Free me from my prison

138
00:16:39,490 --> 00:16:42,500
我就会赐予你力量
and I will grant you the strength

139
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:46,170
好杀死谋害你父亲之人
to kill the man who murdered your father.

140
00:16:46,540 --> 00:16:48,040
你不能这样丢下他
You can't leave him like this!

141
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:50,130
自己去跟大海求饶吧
You ask the sea for mercy.

142
00:16:50,130 --> 00:16:54,550
快走 你得活下去 才能杀了那个混帐
Get out of here! You need to live so you can kill that son of a bitch!

143
00:16:54,550 --> 00:16:59,050
你会夺回他剥夺你的一切
You will take from him what he stole from you.

144
00:17:01,470 --> 00:17:03,980
让他的家园燃烧
His home will burn

145
00:17:03,980 --> 00:17:09,020
让他的王国在我的军团前瓦解
and his kingdom will fall before my legions.

146
00:17:16,990 --> 00:17:18,160
大卫 不要 大卫
David. No, David.

147
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:19,070
大卫
David! Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

148
00:17:19,870 --> 00:17:21,950
大卫 大卫 没事的
David. David, it's okay.

149
00:17:21,950 --> 00:17:23,250
你没事
You're all right.

150
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:27,040
那是什么鬼东西?
What the hell is that thing?

151
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:41,350
（五个月后）

152
00:17:41,350 --> 00:17:44,850
世界各地传来惊人影像
...Just unbelievable footage coming in from all around the world.

153
00:17:44,850 --> 00:17:45,850
各位观众晚安
Good evening, folks.

154
00:17:45,850 --> 00:17:48,850
过去五个月来 世界各地
In the past five months, we've seen an extraordinary rise in temperatures

155
00:17:48,850 --> 00:17:51,230
都传来破纪录的升温
reported around the world.

156
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:55,490
也因此导致许多前所未见的极端气候
And that has resulted in some of the wildest weather we've ever seen.

157
00:17:55,490 --> 00:17:59,070
是的 在德州达拉斯发生了雷雪
Yes, this is thundersnow in Dallas, Texas.

158
00:17:59,070 --> 00:18:03,120
能见度趋近零 今晚预计的降雪量
Visibility is near zero... and there's more snow expected tonight

159
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:06,210
会超过达拉斯往常全年总和
than Dallas usually sees in an entire year.

160
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:09,120
这仅是全球气候异象的一小部分
It's only one part of a worldwide weather phenomenon

161
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:12,000
完全是前所未见
unlike anything we've ever seen before.

162
00:18:17,590 --> 00:18:18,590
亚瑟
Arthur.

163
00:18:22,050 --> 00:18:24,260
议院召开紧急会议
The Council's called for an emergency gathering.

164
00:18:24,810 --> 00:18:26,770
又爆发另一起瘟疫
There's been another plague outbreak.

165
00:18:28,390 --> 00:18:31,560
连科学家都无法解释
...scientists are at a loss to explain.

166
00:18:31,560 --> 00:18:33,520
但真正的问题是
But the real question is,

167
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:37,570
这还会持续多长时间? 气温最后又会有多热?
how long will it continue? And how much hotter is it going to get?

168
00:18:38,740 --> 00:18:40,410
（亚特兰提斯议院）

169
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:42,070
这次是在哪里爆发?
Where did it hit this time?

170
00:18:43,030 --> 00:18:45,120
亚特兰提斯的第九区
The Ninth Tride of Atlantis,

171
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:49,160
现在人鱼王国也传出疫情
and there are now reports of outbreaks in the Fishermen Kingdom as well.

172
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:51,960
已经好几世纪没有这样的疫情
There haven't been outbreaks like this in centuries.

173
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:53,040
为何会现在出现?
Why now?

174
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:57,300
海洋酸化、溶氧量降低、毒性藻华
Increased ocean acidity, decreased oxygen levels, toxic algal blooms.

175
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:59,220
原因任君选择
Take your pick.

176
00:18:59,220 --> 00:19:04,010
陆地居民过去一世纪以来 不断戕害我们环境
The surface has been poisoning our atmosphere for over a century.

177
00:19:04,890 --> 00:19:06,810
若他们不清楚我们的存在
You can't expect them to care about what happens to us

178
00:19:06,810 --> 00:19:08,730
又怎能奢望他们关心我们的处境
if they don't even know we exist.

179
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:11,150
若我们想开始交涉协调
If you want to be a part of the conversation,

180
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:13,480
就得先站出来发声
we have to take our seat at the table.

181
00:19:18,820 --> 00:19:21,740
是时候让亚特兰提斯 在陆地世界前现身了
It's time for Atlantis to reveal itself to the surface.

182
00:19:25,950 --> 00:19:28,910
陛下应该很清楚议院对此举的看法
Your majesty is well aware of the Council's position on this.

183
00:19:28,910 --> 00:19:32,170
听着 我们可以与人类科学家沟通 结合双方科技
Listen, we can talk to their scientists and combine our technologies

184
00:19:32,170 --> 00:19:34,250
来扭转他们所造成的损害
to reverse the damage that they've already done.

185
00:19:35,090 --> 00:19:39,510
我知道这有违我们传统 但这世界正逐渐缩小
And I know this is against our traditions, but the world is shrinking,

186
00:19:39,510 --> 00:19:41,840
传统作法已无法保护我们
and the old ways aren't gonna protect us anymore.

187
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:44,760
时代已经改变
Times have changed.

188
00:19:45,550 --> 00:19:47,140
亚特兰提斯渴望改变
Atlantis wants this.

189
00:19:47,140 --> 00:19:50,020
许多新世代已不愿再躲藏
There's a whole generation out there that don't want to hide anymore.

190
00:19:50,020 --> 00:19:53,350
你难道忘了正是这种瘟疫
Have you already forgotten that this plague

191
00:19:53,350 --> 00:19:56,360
害死了你最敬爱的导师
killed your own beloved mentor,

192
00:19:56,360 --> 00:19:59,900
你现在竟然会想与他们和谈?
and you want to negotiate with them?

193
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:04,410
我们赋予你小弟战争权 与海洋领主的称号不是没有原因的
We gave your brother war powers and made him Ocean Master for a reason.

194
00:20:05,070 --> 00:20:09,120
若我们想让陆地居民知道我们的存在
If we ever decide to make ourselves known to the surface-dwellers,

195
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:13,170
会是为了歼灭他们 而不是共存
it will be to eradicate them, not to co-exist.

196
00:20:41,780 --> 00:20:43,490
厉害吧
Hey, not bad.

197
00:20:45,570 --> 00:20:48,240
我以前哄你睡觉得花两倍时间
Used to take me twice as long to get you to go to sleep.

198
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:50,080
真不知你是怎么办到的 老爸
I don't know how you did it, Pops.

199
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:52,250
梅拉与我有整个王国帮助
Mera and I have the whole kingdom helping us,

200
00:20:52,250 --> 00:20:54,670
但这小家伙还是快把我们整死了
but that little baby boy is still kicking our asses.

201
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:56,080
而你
And you...

202
00:20:57,250 --> 00:21:00,380
独自照顾我 扶养我长大
taking care of me, raising me on your own...

203
00:21:05,090 --> 00:21:06,800
你才是真正的超级英雄
You're the real superhero.

204
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:11,310
敬单亲父母
To single parents.

205
00:21:14,140 --> 00:21:17,440
毕竟我的工作没有你的那么高压
Well, my job was a little less stressful than yours.

206
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:20,150
是喔 但我这工作干得糟透了
Yeah, well, I just plain suck at my job.

207
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:23,490
武尔科嘱咐我要促进海洋与陆地团结
Vulko told me to bring the land and the sea together.

208
00:21:24,650 --> 00:21:29,070
问题是亚特兰提斯 有半数人仍想摧毁陆地
The problem is half of Atlantis still wants to destroy the surface.

209
00:21:29,070 --> 00:21:31,450
他们拒绝沟通 我什么也推动不了
They won't listen. I can't bring shit together.

210
00:21:31,450 --> 00:21:34,580
武尔科相信你 是吧
Vulko believed in you. Aye.

211
00:21:34,580 --> 00:21:35,960
我知道
I know.

212
00:21:38,250 --> 00:21:39,500
我想念他
I miss him.

213
00:21:42,670 --> 00:21:43,670
喂
Hey.

214
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:48,010
你无法拯救每一个人 儿子
You can't save them all, son.

215
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:52,350
你想知道我是怎么独自养大你的?
You really want to know how I raised you here by myself?

216
00:21:54,020 --> 00:21:55,520
我只是埋头苦干
I just kept going.

217
00:21:56,850 --> 00:21:59,610
事情顺利时欢庆 失败时则记取教训
You celebrate the wins, you mourn the losses.

218
00:22:00,150 --> 00:22:02,650
隔天醒来继续加油
And you wake up the next day and you do it again.

219
00:22:02,650 --> 00:22:07,320
有时最勇敢的举动就是永不放弃
Sometimes not giving up is the most heroic thing you can do.

220
00:22:28,470 --> 00:22:34,520
（大西洋某处）

221
00:23:06,300 --> 00:23:08,760
人体构造先天就不该去适应这种深度
Humans were not made to live at these depths.

222
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:11,550
别担心这点
Yeah, don't worry about that.

223
00:23:12,180 --> 00:23:14,510
你只需记得这艘船是谁打造的
You just remember who built this ship.

224
00:23:15,010 --> 00:23:17,810
我比较担心是他们多久前建的
I'm more worried about how long ago they built it.

225
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:22,150
已迫近目标 开启隐形模式
We're coming up on it. Engage stealth mode.

226
00:23:38,950 --> 00:23:40,330
喂 博士
Hey, doc.

227
00:23:41,620 --> 00:23:43,960
快去你那座大炮旁备战
You stand ready with that big gun of yours.

228
00:23:54,390 --> 00:23:57,720
探险日志第613天
Expedition log, day 613.

229
00:23:57,720 --> 00:24:00,310
凯恩踏上我们此行最危险的任务
Kane is off on our most dangerous mission yet.

230
00:24:00,310 --> 00:24:03,150
一个三人的八爪机舰渗透小组
A three man octobot infiltration team.

231
00:24:05,270 --> 00:24:07,480
我们寻获的这些远古机械太神奇了
It's incredible that these ancient machines we found

232
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:09,740
这么多年后仍运作如常
still function after all these years.

233
00:24:09,740 --> 00:24:12,280
我仅为符合需求稍加改造
All I did was retrofit them to our needs.

234
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:16,120
但它们需要一种特殊燃料维持运转
But they require a very specialized fuel to keep them running.

235
00:24:16,120 --> 00:24:18,740
凯恩称之为奥利哈钢
Kane calls it orichalcum.

236
00:24:18,740 --> 00:24:20,580
我不知道他这些知识都是从哪学来的
I don't know how he knows about this,

237
00:24:20,580 --> 00:24:23,290
但从他寻获三叉戟那日就是如此
but it all started the day he found that trident.

238
00:24:23,290 --> 00:24:26,290
突然间他精通以前无从了解的秘辛
Suddenly, he knows secrets that he couldn't possibly know,

239
00:24:26,290 --> 00:24:29,210
包括取得奥利哈钢的唯一管道
including the only way to obtain this orichalcum

240
00:24:29,210 --> 00:24:32,300
就是要从那些高度警戒的贮存场掠夺
is to steal it from highly-protected storage vaults.

241
00:24:32,300 --> 00:24:35,140
我们即将打劫其中最危险的一处
And we're about to hit the most dangerous one of them all.

242
00:25:21,270 --> 00:25:23,640
好 你有15分钟的作业时间
Okay, you have 15 minutes to get in and out.

243
00:25:24,980 --> 00:25:26,730
没有犯错的空间
No margin for error.

244
00:25:41,080 --> 00:25:43,040
从这走应能让你直接抵达
Yeah, this should take you through.

245
00:25:56,970 --> 00:25:58,680
我们不希望发生正面冲突
We don't want any confrontation.

246
00:25:58,680 --> 00:26:01,260
大卫 我们无法对抗他们整个大军
David, we can't fight their entire army.

247
00:26:18,360 --> 00:26:19,280
保持警戒
Stay vigilant.

248
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:22,410
我们不清楚他们有何种的防御机制
We have no idea what kind of security measures they have down there.

249
00:26:34,460 --> 00:26:39,680
（奥利哈钢贮存场）

250
00:26:48,560 --> 00:26:49,850
开始提取
Commencing extraction.

251
00:26:51,060 --> 00:26:53,730
小心点 这东西易燃易爆
Be careful. It's highly volatile.

252
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:02,910
开始装载驳船
Loading barge now.

253
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:23,850
刺魟 改变计划
Stingray, change of plans.

254
00:27:23,850 --> 00:27:25,600
我需要即刻协助撤离
I need an extraction now!

255
00:27:26,470 --> 00:27:28,810
全体进入备战状态
All hands to battle stations.

256
00:27:45,370 --> 00:27:50,120
（亚特兰提斯王国）

257
00:28:02,590 --> 00:28:03,930
太神奇了
Astounding.

258
00:28:08,770 --> 00:28:10,850
不明入侵船舰请注意
Attention, unidentified vessel.

259
00:28:10,850 --> 00:28:13,560
-这里不是过境区域 -博士
- You are out of the transit zone. - Doctor,

260
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:15,150
快点开启音波电池充电
power up the sonic battery.

261
00:28:15,150 --> 00:28:16,940
非法越境将遭受
Illegal border crossing will be met with

262
00:28:16,940 --> 00:28:18,940
-致命武力打击 -现在
- deadly force. - Now!

263
00:28:21,450 --> 00:28:22,860
开始充电
Commencing charge.

264
00:28:29,450 --> 00:28:32,040
边防检查管制 入侵者逼近
Border Control, intruder approaching.

265
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:34,290
武装高压水炮并锁定目标
Arm hydro cannon and lock target.

266
00:28:34,290 --> 00:28:36,790
前边境大门高压水炮已锁定目标
Hydro cannon at front border gate locking in on target.

267
00:28:36,790 --> 00:28:38,340
充电率已设定为最大功率
Chargers set to maximum power.

268
00:28:39,800 --> 00:28:41,720
（防护罩启动）

269
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:42,930
入侵者现身
Intruder in sight.

270
00:28:42,930 --> 00:28:44,300
消灭他们
Take them out!

271
00:28:48,470 --> 00:28:52,140
你们在等什么? 开火啊
What are you waiting for? Fire!

272
00:29:23,090 --> 00:29:25,340
长官 亚特兰提斯敌军正在逼近
Sir, Atlantean hostiles are approaching.

273
00:29:25,930 --> 00:29:28,140
分头行动 自行前往撤离点
Split up. Make your way to the extraction point.

274
00:29:28,140 --> 00:29:29,260
收到
Roger.

275
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:32,390
他们抢了贮存场 我们不能让他们跑了
They've raided the storage vault. We can't let them get away.

276
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:35,270
别担心 他们跑不了 我来追击
Don't worry, they won't. I'm on this one.

277
00:29:49,580 --> 00:29:52,660
暂停开火 他们在穿越夜市
Hold your fire! They're cutting through the Night Market.

278
00:29:52,660 --> 00:29:54,660
小心路人安全
Watch out for the civilians.

279
00:30:49,090 --> 00:30:53,010
警告 警告 非法进入超管区
Warning. Warning. Illegal entrance into hypertube.

280
00:30:53,010 --> 00:30:55,720
超越600节最高限速
Exceeding maximum speed of 600 knots.

281
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:57,770
即刻减速
Reduce speed immediately.

282
00:31:43,900 --> 00:31:44,820
惨了
Oh, shit.

283
00:32:01,080 --> 00:32:03,080
大卫 我们已抵达撤离点
David, we're here at the extraction point.

284
00:32:03,080 --> 00:32:05,040
奥利哈钢已到手并安好
The orichalcum is onboard and secure.

285
00:32:05,040 --> 00:32:06,420
快点 我们走了
Come on, let's go!

286
00:32:06,420 --> 00:32:07,500
不 还不行
Not yet!

287
00:32:07,500 --> 00:32:09,800
我要先杀几个人鱼再走
I'm gonna kill me a dead mermaid.

288
00:32:21,390 --> 00:32:23,560
离我老婆远点
Get away from my wife!

289
00:32:25,230 --> 00:32:26,650
你老婆?
Your wife?

290
00:32:26,650 --> 00:32:29,110
你先是夺走小弟的王位
First you steal your brother's throne,

291
00:32:29,110 --> 00:32:31,030
然后连他女人都抢了?
then you steal his woman?

292
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:34,370
海王 你真可耻
Aquaman, shame on you.

293
00:32:41,540 --> 00:32:42,960
大卫 我们得闪了
Uh, David, we gotta go.

294
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:45,040
整个亚特兰提斯大军正往这赶来
The entire Atlantean army is headed this way.

295
00:32:45,040 --> 00:32:47,040
若我们不现在离开 就死定了
If we don't leave now, we're dead.

296
00:33:34,930 --> 00:33:36,550
左舷20度
Twenty degrees port!

297
00:33:52,740 --> 00:33:54,490
发射音波炮
Fire the sonic cannon!

298
00:33:55,150 --> 00:33:56,320
快啊 老沈
Come on, Shin!

299
00:34:10,210 --> 00:34:13,460
凯鲨夫人在高级议院召开紧急会议
Lady Karshon has called an emergency session of the High Council

300
00:34:13,460 --> 00:34:17,680
以讨论剥夺王座行政权力的动议
to discuss a motion that would strip the throne of its executive power.

301
00:34:17,680 --> 00:34:21,470
王座本该是亚特兰提斯的根本
The throne is the heart of Atlantis.

302
00:34:22,180 --> 00:34:24,730
然而王座现在却经常空虚
Too often now it stands empty,

303
00:34:24,730 --> 00:34:28,350
只因国王有一半时间在陆地游荡
while our king spends half his time on land.

304
00:34:28,730 --> 00:34:32,520
现在他在陆地的仇家更尾随他回家
And now his surface world enemies have followed him home.

305
00:34:33,110 --> 00:34:38,160
若亚特兰提斯在世人面前现身
This tragedy is merely a taste of the havoc that will be wrought,

306
00:34:38,160 --> 00:34:41,910
这次的悲剧只会是冰山一角
if Atlantis ever becomes known to the surface.

307
00:34:41,910 --> 00:34:45,450
因为若他连自己家人都保护不了
Because if he cannot protect his own family,

308
00:34:45,450 --> 00:34:48,540
又如何能保护我们?
how is he supposed to protect us?

309
00:34:55,880 --> 00:34:59,180
他跟之前不同 也更为强大
He's different now. He's stronger than before.

310
00:34:59,180 --> 00:35:01,430
连不穿动力装甲都能跟我对打
And he can fight me without the power suit.

311
00:35:01,430 --> 00:35:03,600
他那些新武器又是从哪来的?
And where the hell did he get all the new toys from?

312
00:35:03,600 --> 00:35:07,430
那些科技看起来很古老 但我们从未见过
The technology seems ancient, but we've never seen anything like it.

313
00:35:07,430 --> 00:35:11,610
他使用的武器射出某种超音波能量
That weapon he used fires some kind of ultrasonic energy

314
00:35:11,610 --> 00:35:13,230
能干扰神经系统
that disrupts the nervous system.

315
00:35:13,230 --> 00:35:14,780
我们知道被盗走什么吗?
Do we know what was stolen?

316
00:35:14,780 --> 00:35:18,990
他带着大量的奥利哈钢库存潜逃了
He escaped with a large stockpile of orichalcum.

317
00:35:20,820 --> 00:35:22,570
我该知道那是什么吗?
Am I supposed to know what that is?

318
00:35:22,570 --> 00:35:25,830
奥利哈钢是远古时代使用的能量源
Orichalcum is a power source that was used in ancient times.

319
00:35:25,830 --> 00:35:28,500
会排放大量的温室气体
It emits tremendous amounts of greenhouse gases

320
00:35:28,500 --> 00:35:30,330
对地球造成重大伤害
that are highly destructive to our planet.

321
00:35:30,330 --> 00:35:33,210
事实上 在我们察觉这点前
In fact, we almost destroyed the oceans ourselves

322
00:35:33,210 --> 00:35:35,050
我们自己也差点毁了海洋
before we realized what we were doing.

323
00:35:36,010 --> 00:35:39,550
这物质无法被安全处置 所以我们将剩余的库存
It can't be disposed of safely, so the remaining stockpile

324
00:35:39,550 --> 00:35:43,220
分别埋在地底深处的12个贮存场中
has been buried in 12 storage vaults deep underground.

325
00:35:43,220 --> 00:35:45,060
我们该警告其他的贮存场
We should warn the other places that are storing the stuff.

326
00:35:45,060 --> 00:35:47,810
他早就打劫过了 库存全没了
He's already been there. It's all gone.

327
00:35:47,810 --> 00:35:51,650
我们认为他过去五个月 一直在暗中袭击
We think he's been launching secret raids for at least five months.

328
00:35:51,650 --> 00:35:53,230
只是这次不小心被抓到
This is just the time he got caught.

329
00:35:53,230 --> 00:35:56,900
这波全球气温飙高 在陆地酿灾
Well, this spike in global temperatures that's causing disasters on the surface

330
00:35:56,900 --> 00:36:01,160
并让陆地居民生病的灾情 也是五个月前开始的
and making the sea dwellers sick happened five months ago.

331
00:36:01,820 --> 00:36:04,950
他用偷来的奥利哈钢来加速地球暖化
He's using the stolen orichalcum to heat the planet.

332
00:36:07,160 --> 00:36:08,750
他为何要如此?
Why would he do that?

333
00:36:08,750 --> 00:36:10,580
我不知道 但我会查个清楚
I don't know, but I'm gonna find out.

334
00:36:10,580 --> 00:36:13,130
若他在用奥利哈钢加温地球
If he is using the orichalcum to heat the planet,

335
00:36:13,130 --> 00:36:14,290
我们的时间就不多了
we don't have much time.

336
00:36:14,290 --> 00:36:16,420
他已将此效应推越临界点
He is pushing this past the tipping point.

337
00:36:16,420 --> 00:36:21,010
我们必须阻止他 不然全球气候崩盘迫在眉睫
He must be stopped or a global climate meltdown is imminent.

338
00:36:21,010 --> 00:36:23,890
我们需要找到他 但他目前消失无踪
We need to find him, but he's completely vanished off the radar.

339
00:36:23,890 --> 00:36:26,640
我想我知道有谁能帮助我们
I think I know someone who might be able to help us.

340
00:36:27,640 --> 00:36:29,060
但你们肯定不会喜欢
But you're not gonna like it.

341
00:36:30,680 --> 00:36:31,810
你小弟?
Your brother?

